            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong>, 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[320ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong>, the<strong> outer lemongrass layers </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving – this is your <strong>lemongrass rice</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1602611418223-x200.jpg",
